                          {/* Replace HoverCard */}
                          <span class="cursor-help text-blue-600 relative group"> {/* Adjusted color */}
                            industrial designer
                            <span class="absolute hidden group-hover:block bg-black text-white text-xs rounded py-1 px-2 bottom-full left-1/2 transform -translate-x-1/2 mb-1 w-80 z-10">
                                <strong class="font-semibold">Industrial Designer</strong><br/>
                                A professional who designs products for mass production, with a focus on both form and function.
                            </span>
                          </span>
                          closely associated with the consumer products company Braun and functionalist industrial design.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                          According to Vitsoe: Back in the early 1980s, aware that his design was a significant contributor
                          to the world, he asked himself an important question: "Is my design good design?"
                        </p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="md:w-2/3">
                        <p class="mb-4">
                          Since good design can't be measured in a finite way, he set about expressing the ten most important
                          principles for what he considered was good design. (Sometimes they are referred as the Ten commandments.)
                          Here they are.
                        </p>
                        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-6">
                          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-md">
                            <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Good design is innovative</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Technological advancement always offers new opportunities for design.</p> {/* Adjusted color */}
                          </div>
                          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-md">
                            <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Good design makes a product useful</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Products are bought to be used. Design should enhance function.</p> {/* Adjusted color */}
                          </div>
                          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-md">
                            <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Good design is aesthetic</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">The aesthetic quality is integral to usefulness.</p> {/* Adjusted color */}
                          </div>
                          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-md">
                            <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Good design makes a product understandable</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Products should communicate their function.</p> {/* Adjusted color */}
                          </div>
                          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-md">
                            <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Good design is unobtrusive</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Products should be neutral and allow users to express themselves.</p> {/* Adjusted color */}
                          </div>
                          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-md">
                            <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Good design is honest</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Design should not manipulate users with false promises.</p> {/* Adjusted color */}
                          </div>
                          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-md">
                            <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Good design is long-lasting</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">It avoids being fashionable and therefore never appears antiquated.</p> {/* Adjusted color */}
                          </div>
                          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-md">
                            <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Good design is thorough</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Nothing must be arbitrary or left to chance. Every detail matters.</p> {/* Adjusted color */}
                          </div>
                          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-md">
                            <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Good design is environmentally friendly</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Design should conserve resources and minimize pollution.</p> {/* Adjusted color */}
                          </div>
                          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-md">
                            <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Good design is as little design as possible</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Less, but better – because it concentrates on the essential aspects.</p> {/* Adjusted color */}
                          </div>
                        </div>
