                      We designers, we don't work in a vacuum. We need business people. We are not the fine artists we are
                      often confused with. Today you find few companies that take design seriously, as I see it.
                      <footer class="mt-2 font-medium not-italic">Dieter Rams</footer> {/* Make footer not italic */}
                    </blockquote>
                  </div>

                  <div id="sec14" class="mb-12">
                     {/* Removed extra h2 */}
                    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 mt-6"> {/* Added mt-6 for spacing */}
                      <span class="text-blue-600 font-medium">1.4</span> Good design can't be achieved with glossy buttons or masterful wireframes alone. It's a merger of all
